# No PII / secrets / rate data in logs

## Rule
Freight data is commercial, not personal, but the following never appear in logs at INFO+ or in error-report payloads:
- Raw rate rows (freight rates, surcharges, DnD rates).
- JWT / access tokens / refresh tokens.
- API keys (`fbratesgoapikey`, `fbiqsapikey`, `RATE_AGENT_API_KEY`, `QA_AGENT_API_KEY`, `BACKEND_SERVICE_API_KEY`, `JIRA_API_TOKEN`).
- Customer email bodies, shipper names, consignee names (Quote AI path).
- Raw LLM prompts / responses containing the above.

DEBUG level may include redacted versions during local development; production level is INFO.

## Why
Every `security.md` in the workspace calls out these categories. Logs flow into CloudWatch / Google Cloud Logging / Sentry / Airbrake — multiple systems with different access controls and retention. One leaky line can violate a customer's commercial-in-confidence terms.

## Constraints
- Log IDs and counts, not payloads: `{tariffId, vendorId, rowCount: 412}` not `{rows: [...]}`.
- Tokens and keys are either logged as `***` or as the first 6 characters followed by `***`.
- Sentry / Airbrake `beforeSend` hooks scrub known-sensitive field names workspace-wide (`token`, `apiKey`, `password`, `rate`, `freight`).
- LLM call logging captures model, token counts, latency, and prompt hash — never the prompt text at INFO+.

## Examples

### Good
```ts
logger.info("search completed", { correlationId, vendorId, resultCount: 42 });
```

### Bad
```ts
logger.info("search", { correlationId, results }); // raw rate rows leak
```

